Abstract = {Forensics is an important topic for civil, academics, and software
   professionals who deal with very complex investigations. Today there is
   increases usage of big data technologies such as hadoop in all sectors
   like BFSI, oil energy, etc. for analytics. Forensic investigators have
   required new approaches to how analysis conducted also need to
   understand how to work with big data solutions/technologies. The number
   of organizations who implemented big data solutions had spent lots of
   time for forensic investigation by using of traditional forensic
   approach. These big data clusters contain critical information that
   provides information about organization's strategies and operations.
   Since hadoop has distributed architecture, in memory data storage and
   huge volume of data, forensic on hadoop offers new challenges to
   investigators. Big data forensic is a new area within forensic which
   focuses on the forensics of big data systems. Since big data are
   scalable, high volume of data, which provides practical limitation for
   forensic investigation by using traditional approaches. Big data
   Forensic analytics provides new approaches to collect data, for
   analyzing collected data.},
