   (AIES), St Josephs Coll Engn \& Technol, Palai, INDIA, DEC 08-09, 2021},
Abstract = {Most of the modern-day industries like food processing, steam power
   plants, etc. are explicitly powered in conjunction with prime movers
   that generate steam or compressed air. The perverse of the prime movers
   persist on their obligation of frequent fuel loading, thus performed in
   conjunction with only with man's workforce. The complied manpower when
   detected at the same time employed produce tenacious thoracic and lumbar
   bend angles intending to develop and inculcate musculoskeletal
   disorders. The assessment of the stance utilized by the workers is
   critical and crucial in the evaluation and risk prevention at spinal and
   vertebrae. This article delivers the ergonomic assessment of manpower at
   the fuel dumping by victimization methods acknowledged as RULA (Rapid
   Upper Body Assessment) and REBA (Rapid Entire Body Assessment) and
   affords a proposal of low expenditure to enhance the competence and
   proficiency of the manpower and lessen the prospects of musculoskeletal
   disorders.Copyright (c) 2022 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
