Abstract = {Phishingis a fraudulent process and a form of cybercrime where an
   attacker tries to obtain sensitive information for malicious use. A
   phisher uses social engineering and technical deception to fetch private
   information from the web user. Previous Machine Learning (ML) approaches
   have been used to detect whether URLs are valid, or invalid. The purpose
   of this work is to detect, or predict, the three stages of Phishing URLs
   starting with valid, not enough info and invalid URLs. We will
   investigate different potential models that are trained by Machine
   Learning algorithms and find out which of these models has better
   accuracy.},
